# 3. Difference Between BACnet/IP and BACnet MS/TP

| Feature        | BACnet/IP       | BACnet MS/TP  |
| -------------- | --------------- | ------------- |
| Physical Layer | Ethernet        | RS-485        |
| Speed          | High            | Lower         |
| Topology       | Star/Switched   | Daisy chain   |
| Communication  | IP-based        | Token passing |
| Distance       | LAN/WAN capable | Limited       |
| Cost           | Higher          | Lower         |
| Scalability    | High            | Moderate      |

---

# BACnet/IP Detailed Explanation

Uses:

* UDP/IP
* Ethernet infrastructure

Port:

* Default UDP 47808

Advantages:

* Faster communication
* Easy integration
* Remote connectivity

Common Devices:

* BMS controllers
* HVAC systems

---

# BACnet MS/TP Detailed Explanation

MS/TP = Master Slave/Token Passing

Uses:

* RS485 serial communication

Key Concept:
A token circulates between devices.
Only token owner can transmit.

Advantages:

* Reliable
* Cost-effective

Disadvantages:

* Slower
* More troubleshooting complexity

---

# Common Interview Question:

## Why token passing?

Prevents:

* Data collision
* Bus contention

Ensures deterministic communication.

