# 10. Explain VFD Working Principle

VFD = Variable Frequency Drive

Purpose:
Control AC motor speed by varying:

* Frequency
* Voltage

---

# Working Stages

## Step 1: Rectifier

AC → DC

Uses:

* Diodes
* Thyristors

---

## Step 2: DC Bus

Stores filtered DC voltage.

Components:

* Capacitors
* Inductors

---

## Step 3: Inverter

DC → Variable frequency AC

Uses:

* IGBTs
* PWM switching

---

# Motor Speed Formula

Using synchronous speed relation:

N_s = \frac{120f}{P}

Where:

* (N_s) = synchronous speed
* (f) = frequency
* (P) = poles

Increasing frequency increases motor speed.

---

# Advantages of VFD

* Energy savings
* Soft starting
* Reduced mechanical stress
* Better process control

---

# 11. Difference Between VFD and Soft Starter

| Feature             | VFD    | Soft Starter |
| ------------------- | ------ | ------------ |
| Speed Control       | Yes    | No           |
| Frequency Variation | Yes    | No           |
| Energy Saving       | High   | Moderate     |
| Cost                | Higher | Lower        |
| Torque Control      | Better | Limited      |

---

# Soft Starter Purpose

Reduces:

* Inrush current
* Mechanical shock

During startup only.

