# 12. Explain Profinet RT vs IRT

# RT (Real Time)

Used for:

* Standard automation

Cycle time:

* ~10 ms

---

# IRT (Isochronous Real Time)

Used for:

* Motion control
* Servo synchronization

Cycle time:

* <1 ms

Provides:

* Very low jitter
* Deterministic timing

---

# Key Difference

IRT reserves bandwidth and schedules traffic precisely.

